manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: KUNMI Women's Flare Bell Bottom Jeans High Waisted Wide Leg Bootcut Jeans Stretchy Denim Pants Give your look a touch of the 70’s with this edit of flared jeans. A pair of women’s flared jeans is so on-trend right now so you you’ll be looking your best no matter the occasion. Whether you’re looking to update your denim collection or if flares are just your thing, this range of flared jeans is sure to take your look to new heights. From bleach washes right though to black flare jeans, we have got every hue, shape and size covered with our flare styles. Style a pair of bell bottom jeans with a simple crop top and ankle boots for the ultimate off-duty look. For a catch up with your besties, team a pair of white or blue flare jeans with a slogan tee, strappy heels, and simple accessories for a seriously chic combo. Opt for a pair if high waisted flare jeans or work a pair of low rise flare jeans for a look we’re loving. From kick flare jeans to distressed bell bottoms and skinny flare jeans, whatever occasion you’ve got planned make sure a pair of our women’s flared jeans is on your wishlist this season.

Flared jeans make the perfect weekend outfit. Straight out of the ‘70s and into 2023, this is a jean trend not to shy away from, girl. Whether you’re pairing cropped flare jeans with an oversized t-shirt and trainers or you're styling out a pair of high waisted flared jeans with heeled boots, we've got the shape you need right here. Seen in stretch materials and split hem styles, bell bottom jeans are the versatile vintage piece you need. From kick flare shapes to iconic blue washes, upgrade your denim collection and choose your fave look from our women’s flare jeans edit.

Are you short or do you have relatively short legs? Flared styles are a perfect choice, because of the leg-lengthen effect. Do you have beautiful long legs? Make them even longer and create a streamlined silhouette. Check out our style suggestions: 1. Wear flared pants with heels. Combine the pants with beautiful heels. Next to the leg-lengthen effect, you also will create a chic feel. Bring the 70’s back into your outfit with block-heeled ankle boots. Combine with pointed pumps for a business look. 2. Wear a top into your pants. Wear a slouchy top nonchalant into your flared pants. For a cool laidback vibe and accentuate your feminine silhouette. Complement with an eye-catching belt. 3. Style the pants with classic pieces. Create a classic look and combine the flared pants with a simple basic top. Complement the look with a tonal blazer and create on-duty appeal. 4. Create a high-fashion seventies look. Opt for a seventies revival and choose high-rise flared pants. Wear the pants with a loose-fitted shirt with trumpet sleeves or pair with a turtleneck pullover. Combine the look with chunky block-heeled ankle boots. Complement this fall with chunky knits; for example an oversized cardigan or a poncho-scarf.

My biggest tip to styling this silhouette is to look for a few things. First, high waisted. I just think they’re more flattering and allow a longer line on your body. Second, get them tailored to work with your preferred shoes. You want them to just kiss the ground. No higher, but can definitely go longer and have them puddle a bit. And lastly, balance. If your pant leg is super wide, keep things more tailored and fitted up top. It’ll be less overwhelming on your body and be much more flattering.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality, Fit, and Comfort
reviews.reviewText: Love these, cute fit, true to size, run a little on the longer side which is great for taller people and for platformed or heeled shoes.Material and fit; there’s no compromise you get both the stretchy fit and still real Denim. Cute buttons to secure. Flattering cut and the stretch makes them feel more relaxed for any setting.I hadn’t noticed the pattern before purchasing, but it works with the color I got just fine. I wouldn’t likely purchase it again, as it goes into almost a stone washy design at the flares of each leg, but it’s cute and unique.Overall, highly recommend and especially for the price! Well worth it. Buy the jeans for yourself!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These are nice and stretchy. Very comfortable. I wish the vintage/ripped look was more profound on the hem, but I think with more washes that'll happen. The length and size are both good for me. I'm 5'4" 185 lbs. I got a 12. I think they'd look good with better shoes than in my pic...Overall, I'm glad I bought these. Needed comfortable jeans and these serve the purpose.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I LOVE these jeans! These are my new fav by far!! I recently lost 75 pounds so had no idea what my size was, i have been wearing maternity jeans for a decade! I had to return 3 times!! Started with a 16, then 14, then 12, these are a 10!! The return process with UPS could NOT be easier and zero issues. I was never questioned. I am 5’3 174 pounds. The length is perfect, so hard to find any pants that don't have a few inches dragging on floor. they have stretch, they hug in all the right places. Plus just mad style, very cool. I have gotten so many compliments on them. Even the wear, the distressing makes it seem like i’ve had these as my fav for years. I will be ordering more pairs ASAP! These are a MUST BUY! You will not regret!! I have tried probably 15 different brands, this is the ONLY pair I have loved top to bottom. Oh! And sooo soft and easy to move in. Photo with white top is how they looked after wearing them every day for a week! I know i know, gross, which is why I will be buying more pairs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Good fit but too large on my hips also too long I sent them back

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 12, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars What a fit!!!!
reviews.reviewText: These jeans have just the right amount of stretch and the fit is perfect.They are so comfortable and stylish.The wide leg is not too wide and can be worn with flats, wedges, and ankle boots.The price is awesome.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These jeans are great! Nice stretch, hug all the right places! Even the waist fits me great as I typically have a gap with jeans in the waist, but not these. They are the perfect length as well. I’m 5’3” and 175 lbs. I will definitely be buying another pair!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 13, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars comfortable and sort of flattering
reviews.reviewText: I will keep these. They fit like they look in the picture. Close at the knees and then flare out at the bottom. However they were a tad bit too long. If I wear a shoe with a heel it helps. otherwise they brush the floor as I stand and walk. They also were a bit big in the waist, but a belt will help with this. I am 5'7 1/2". I am about 120 pounds. My legs are a little longer than average. I got a size 4. Very comfortable too!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Doesn’t look naturally worn
reviews.reviewText: The I only reason I gave these jeans a 3 is because they are stretchy and super comfortable. They fit to size. Not the best quality but would be worth the price if the bleaching looked like more natural wear. There are very clearly intentional ovals both in the front AND the back. The pictures don’t show them being as “worn” on the backside as they tried to make them look. I’m returning but will try a different color / wash in the hopes that they work out because the fur was perfect.
